  "conformsToProfile": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileMinimal",
  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01)",
  "description": "Minimal-profile UnitOfAssurance for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The governing requirement (REQ-VAD-HEM-001) mandates that predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values remain within ±15% of bench measurements across the VAD operating envelope (2000–3500 RPM, 2–8 L/min). The associated claim asserts that the SST k-ω CFD model with power-law hemolysis correlation meets this requirement at Model Risk Level 5 for a Class III implantable device. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; seven factors are fully assessed and six are flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo UQ confirms sensitivity bounds. Decision: Accepted at Low assurance level pending gap closure plan.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hem-nih-accuracy-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/sst-komega-nih-within-15pct-vad-envelope",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-sst-komega-powerlaw-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-benchmark-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-measurements",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/vad-operating-envelope-monte-carlo-samples"
  ],
